WEBVTT

00:50.049 --> 00:52.469
ALL FIGURES, INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,
ORGANIZATIONS, AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS

00:52.552 --> 00:54.971
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS WERE FILMED
SAFELY IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES

00:56.097 --> 00:57.265
Mr. Kang.

01:03.563 --> 01:04.731
Are you all right?

01:05.231 --> 01:07.442
Who are you, young man?

01:08.693 --> 01:09.778
What?

01:10.445 --> 01:11.446
Wait.

01:12.822 --> 01:13.907
Where am I?

01:25.543 --> 01:26.544
What is it?

01:27.128 --> 01:29.672
He doesn't remember.

01:33.551 --> 01:35.261
Our client disappeared,

01:35.887 --> 01:37.889
and the will turned out to be fabricated.

01:37.972 --> 01:39.974
We have no standing
to continue with this suit.

01:41.309 --> 01:45.730
Still, let's not give up
and wait until Ms. Chae shows up.

01:46.272 --> 01:47.774
I'm sorry.

01:49.609 --> 01:50.610
Ms. Chae.

01:51.945 --> 01:53.321
Are you okay?

01:57.867 --> 01:59.327
Have a seat here.

01:59.410 --> 02:00.245
Thanks.

02:10.672 --> 02:12.006
I'm sorry.

02:13.758 --> 02:15.176
Did you really tell your husband

02:16.177 --> 02:17.971
what to write in his last will?

02:19.639 --> 02:20.682
I did.

02:21.891 --> 02:23.476
I told him what to write,

02:24.310 --> 02:26.020
and he wrote what I said.

02:26.646 --> 02:27.647
Ms. Chae.

02:29.524 --> 02:31.818
Why did you report Ms. Ryeo?

02:33.194 --> 02:35.697
You mentioned that she was like family.

02:49.460 --> 02:54.090
I fell in love with my husband
at first sight.

02:54.716 --> 02:56.467
IDEAL SHOES

03:02.348 --> 03:03.892
After meeting him,

03:04.434 --> 03:08.479
I realized he was even
more wonderful than I'd imagined.

03:08.563 --> 03:11.482
-Are you okay?
-Yes, I'm all right. Thank you.

03:13.067 --> 03:14.027
Oh, goodness.

03:14.110 --> 03:16.863
My feelings for him
grew bigger and bigger.

03:17.363 --> 03:19.741
-I made up my mind to tell him how I felt…
-Are you not hurt?

03:19.824 --> 03:22.785
-I'm okay.
-…regardless of how the result would be.

03:22.869 --> 03:23.912
Take care, sir.

03:24.495 --> 03:25.622
And then,

03:26.664 --> 03:27.832
I saw him

03:28.708 --> 03:31.586
make these red shoes.

03:35.089 --> 03:39.594
I was elated, thinking they were for me.

03:40.553 --> 03:41.804
Are you done?

03:42.430 --> 03:44.474
Yes, I'm almost done.

03:44.557 --> 03:47.310
But… they weren't.

03:47.393 --> 03:49.062
They're beautiful.

03:49.145 --> 03:50.188
He was…

03:50.271 --> 03:51.272
Aren't they?

03:51.356 --> 03:53.316
…with Seon Hwa there.

03:55.318 --> 03:57.946
Out of frustration,
I went straight to a bar.

03:59.739 --> 04:02.408
There's a man I like.

04:05.203 --> 04:07.789
But he likes someone else.

04:09.165 --> 04:11.584
Why does he even like someone
who has a child up north?

04:12.377 --> 04:13.670
-Seon Hwa!
-No, I…

04:13.753 --> 04:15.630
-A few days later…
-Seon Hwa!

04:15.713 --> 04:17.548
…Seon Hwa was arrested.

04:17.632 --> 04:18.591
Get her in.

04:19.550 --> 04:20.593
North?

04:20.677 --> 04:22.011
You mean North Korea?

04:22.595 --> 04:23.554
It was that man.

04:23.638 --> 04:25.682
-Seon Hwa!
-Mr. Kang.

04:25.765 --> 04:26.933
Seon Hwa!

04:27.767 --> 04:30.770
From then on, I wasn't in my right mind.

04:31.896 --> 04:35.149
I could neither eat nor sleep.

04:36.234 --> 04:40.196
I couldn't face Dong-sik at all.

04:49.372 --> 04:50.665
But one day,

04:51.457 --> 04:54.043
he came to me and said…

04:54.127 --> 04:55.545
Don't be sad anymore.

04:56.379 --> 04:58.256
I'm afraid
something will happen to you too.

04:59.590 --> 05:04.304
It was more devastating
because I couldn't tell him what I'd done.

05:05.930 --> 05:07.557
Nevertheless,

05:08.182 --> 05:10.977
he tried to comfort me somehow.

05:11.561 --> 05:13.646
Embracing each other's broken hearts,

05:14.355 --> 05:16.649
we became closer over time.

05:18.901 --> 05:21.571
With that shattered heart, I married him.

05:22.655 --> 05:26.409
I even birthed his child.
And lived 50 years like that.

05:28.161 --> 05:29.829
Throughout that time,

05:29.912 --> 05:34.042
he adored me as his wife
and the mother of Ji-hoon.

05:35.043 --> 05:35.960
But…

05:37.336 --> 05:41.674
I couldn't free myself from the guilt
that the woman he loved

05:41.758 --> 05:43.384
died because of me.

05:46.095 --> 05:47.889
So I made up my mind

05:48.473 --> 05:49.849
that one day

05:50.892 --> 05:54.896
I'd find Seon Hwa's son
and give him her rightful share.

05:56.647 --> 05:58.232
I wanted to pay the price of my sin

05:59.484 --> 06:01.569
at least a little by doing so.

06:06.074 --> 06:07.700
I understand how you feel.

06:08.326 --> 06:12.538
But now that your husband's will
turned out to be fake,

06:12.622 --> 06:15.458
the suit will be closed.

06:16.125 --> 06:17.001
Then,

06:18.419 --> 06:22.048
will I not be able to give money
to Seon Hwa's son?

06:22.131 --> 06:26.177
I'll suggest the plaintiff's attorney
moral settlement money.

06:26.260 --> 06:28.096
That won't be easy.

06:28.179 --> 06:31.974
CEO Kang must be upset
about the fabrication of the will,

06:32.683 --> 06:34.060
and he won't likely give credit

06:34.143 --> 06:36.771
to the contribution of someone
who died 40 years ago.

06:39.107 --> 06:40.066
Well…

06:42.193 --> 06:45.029
I know

06:45.113 --> 06:47.323
it sounds ridiculous,

06:48.199 --> 06:49.033
but if…

06:50.451 --> 06:51.536
What happens if

06:52.453 --> 06:56.582
Seon Hwa is alive?

06:59.001 --> 07:00.753
What do you mean by that?

07:02.296 --> 07:04.757
I went to her grave

07:06.217 --> 07:09.220
to bury these shoes next to her.

07:13.307 --> 07:14.267
Seon Hwa.

07:17.353 --> 07:19.188
I know it's too late,

07:21.315 --> 07:24.402
but I want to give these back to you.

07:32.785 --> 07:34.704
I'm sorry, Seon Hwa.

08:03.566 --> 08:05.985
THANK YOU, JEONG-HUI

08:06.569 --> 08:07.653
Seon Hwa?

08:10.698 --> 08:11.616
Seon Hwa…

08:14.076 --> 08:15.495
Seon Hwa!

08:15.578 --> 08:17.038
That place…

08:18.372 --> 08:22.960
My husband, Seon Hwa, and me.

08:23.711 --> 08:26.923
Only the three of us
know about that place.

08:28.424 --> 08:31.969
I'm sure she left this message.

08:38.142 --> 08:40.645
THANK YOU, JEONG-HUI

08:43.314 --> 08:47.235
If Ms. Ryeo is alive,
it'll be a complete game-changer.

08:49.362 --> 08:50.530
Right, Attorney Han?

08:50.613 --> 08:53.032
It's possible if she's alive.

08:53.658 --> 08:56.911
But it won't be easy to find someone
with just a message she left behind.

08:57.787 --> 08:59.914
I'm sorry. Let me excuse myself.

09:00.498 --> 09:01.707
But…

09:03.793 --> 09:04.794
Just a moment, please.

09:23.563 --> 09:25.523
I know you're frustrated and angry.

09:26.357 --> 09:27.525
But then,

09:28.317 --> 09:29.777
it's such a pity.

09:30.361 --> 09:31.279
Who do you mean?

09:32.363 --> 09:33.281
All of them.

09:34.240 --> 09:35.741
Ms. Chae, her husband,

09:36.784 --> 09:38.119
and Ms. Ryeo.

09:44.625 --> 09:45.960
I'll go talk to Taebaek.

09:47.003 --> 09:50.673
If they offer a settlement,
let's take it and be done with it.

09:51.299 --> 09:52.425
Okay?

09:55.344 --> 09:56.679
TAEBAEK

09:56.762 --> 09:59.015
Now that the will turned out to be fake,

09:59.098 --> 10:01.642
the other party will agree
to end this lawsuit.

10:01.726 --> 10:05.813
And Cha Eun Seong will be satisfied
with some consolation money.

10:09.275 --> 10:12.737
Of course, you don't have to give a dime
if you don't want to.

10:12.820 --> 10:14.530
Why didn't you tell me

10:15.615 --> 10:17.533
that my mother reported Ms. Ryeo

10:19.160 --> 10:20.911
and that she died in prison?

10:24.373 --> 10:27.335
I apologize
for not telling you in advance,

10:27.418 --> 10:29.670
but that was out of consideration for you.

10:29.754 --> 10:31.881
In case you felt any unnecessary emotions.

10:31.964 --> 10:33.466
Unnecessary emotions?

10:35.092 --> 10:36.761
Emotions that may hinder your trial

10:36.844 --> 10:40.222
such as a sense of guilt,
indebtedness, sympathy, or compassion.

10:41.724 --> 10:45.311
Your goal was to protect
your father's estate, wasn't it?

10:46.020 --> 10:48.397
I simply did my best for that goal.

10:49.982 --> 10:51.651
What will you do about settlement money?

10:51.734 --> 10:53.444
If you have a certain amount in mind--

10:53.527 --> 10:56.656
Whether it be settlement
or consolation money, I'll decide later.

10:57.239 --> 10:58.616
I need to meet my mother first.

10:59.617 --> 11:00.618
Goodbye.

11:07.375 --> 11:09.710
He wants to see his mother
in this situation?

11:14.924 --> 11:17.385
Sir, Attorney Han is here to see you.

11:18.928 --> 11:19.929
Okay.

11:26.894 --> 11:28.396
You came sooner than expected.

11:29.939 --> 11:31.607
How's your father? Is he doing well?

11:33.484 --> 11:34.860
Did you expect me to come?

11:35.528 --> 11:37.071
Yes, of course.

11:37.947 --> 11:40.908
I got your original office
all ready for you too.

11:41.534 --> 11:45.413
So stop wasting your time
and work with me.

11:45.496 --> 11:48.666
I'll stop wasting my time
and get straight to the point.

11:49.834 --> 11:51.377
Let's put an end to this lawsuit.

11:56.215 --> 11:57.633
LIST OF COLLECTED EVIDENCE

11:57.716 --> 11:59.552
I know one-third is too much.

11:59.635 --> 12:03.305
But it's clear that Ms. Ryeo made
contributions to Ideal Shoes.

12:03.389 --> 12:04.598
There's enough evidence.

12:06.183 --> 12:10.312
What do you say about
settling to 10% of the total assets?

12:13.482 --> 12:16.110
You converted the contributions
of someone who died 40 years ago

12:16.193 --> 12:18.070
into today's value?

12:21.699 --> 12:24.827
This ridiculous idea can't be yours.

12:25.369 --> 12:26.662
Is it Shin I-rang's idea?

12:26.745 --> 12:30.082
It's neither ridiculous nor his idea.

12:35.588 --> 12:39.633
I wonder what changed
the rational and cool-headed Attorney Han.

12:41.886 --> 12:45.181
Shin I-rang acted weird in court again.
You saw it too.

12:46.015 --> 12:48.601
I told you. He's dangerous to be around.

12:49.685 --> 12:51.812
You're not like him.

12:51.896 --> 12:55.191
The two of you are like oil and water.
You're cut from a different cloth.

12:56.817 --> 12:57.818
You're right.

12:59.236 --> 13:01.155
Attorney Shin is different from me.

13:03.741 --> 13:05.201
That's why I like being with him.

13:07.328 --> 13:08.162
What about me?

13:09.580 --> 13:10.414
Excuse me?

13:12.458 --> 13:13.792
I mean,

13:13.876 --> 13:15.252
Taebaek

13:16.420 --> 13:18.047
also needs an attorney like you.

13:18.923 --> 13:21.675
Taebaek has a lot of better attorneys.

13:21.759 --> 13:22.968
Whatever. Forget it.

13:24.512 --> 13:27.139
Come back to Taebaek, or no settlement.
That's final.

13:27.223 --> 13:28.724
Don't be childish.

13:28.807 --> 13:30.518
You knew I was childish.

13:30.601 --> 13:32.686
You told me off for it all the time.

13:35.981 --> 13:37.024
Fine.

13:37.775 --> 13:41.654
If you won't agree to settle,
we'll find another way.

13:44.990 --> 13:46.242
What way?

13:48.577 --> 13:49.578
What is it?

13:56.168 --> 13:58.587
The prison doesn't have
any records of Seon Hwa?

13:59.338 --> 14:00.214
No.

14:02.341 --> 14:05.594
Fair enough. It's been such a long time.

14:07.555 --> 14:08.430
Anyway,

14:09.682 --> 14:11.559
if she's alive,

14:12.142 --> 14:14.728
I wonder whose ashes are
buried in the grave.

14:15.479 --> 14:18.190
Who gave you the ashes?

14:18.816 --> 14:21.652
Seon Hwa's attorney brought the urn to me.

14:21.735 --> 14:24.405
He called himself a public defender.

14:25.072 --> 14:27.908
But I don't remember
his name or phone number

14:27.992 --> 14:30.911
because it's been so long.

14:33.038 --> 14:34.498
I found a way.

14:35.624 --> 14:38.002
-Oh, my.
-Through the Bar Association,

14:38.085 --> 14:40.045
we may be able
to find the public defenders

14:40.129 --> 14:42.506
who visited Anyang Prison
around that time.

14:42.590 --> 14:45.426
One of them should be
Ms. Ryeo's former attorney.

14:47.553 --> 14:48.846
My goodness.

14:53.976 --> 14:55.978
Did the settlement fall through?

14:57.313 --> 14:58.188
Yes.

14:58.814 --> 15:00.316
Let's give up on this suit.

15:00.983 --> 15:02.943
If we continue,
we'll be at a disadvantage.

15:04.820 --> 15:05.905
I agree.

15:06.739 --> 15:09.366
But I'm thinking
of filing a new suit instead.

15:10.534 --> 15:11.911
A new suit?

15:11.994 --> 15:15.080
A suit for a provisional injunction
on profit distribution

15:15.164 --> 15:18.959
with Ms. Ryeo's son,
Cha Eun Seong, as the plaintiff.

15:21.211 --> 15:22.338
That's not bad.

15:23.213 --> 15:27.635
We might have a chance if we can
find Ms. Ryeo and get her to testify.

15:28.344 --> 15:29.553
Exactly.

15:32.556 --> 15:34.099
What a relief.

15:40.648 --> 15:41.523
Excuse me.

15:42.107 --> 15:43.108
Are you tired?

15:43.192 --> 15:47.363
I couldn't sleep much for a few days
preparing the petition.

15:48.989 --> 15:49.990
Do you want

15:51.367 --> 15:52.284
some of this?

15:52.368 --> 15:53.494
COFFEE CANDY

15:53.577 --> 15:55.871
Oh, this.

16:07.633 --> 16:08.884
I'm suddenly wide wake.

16:11.095 --> 16:12.221
It's tasty.

16:13.847 --> 16:15.224
Is it because it's from you?

16:20.521 --> 16:23.565
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

16:24.358 --> 16:29.321
I'm looking for public defenders
with a history of visiting Anyang Prison

16:29.405 --> 16:31.240
between 1983 and 1985.

16:31.323 --> 16:33.659
Is this Attorney Jeon Gyeong-hyeop?

16:35.285 --> 16:40.040
Do you perhaps know a woman
named Ryeo Seon Hwa

16:40.124 --> 16:42.084
who served time in Anyang Prison in 1983?

16:42.167 --> 16:44.461
SUSHI

16:45.921 --> 16:48.716
This won't do.
We better contact them one by one.

16:48.799 --> 16:50.384
I agree.

16:54.054 --> 16:57.599
Let's forget about work
while we're eating, though.

16:58.767 --> 16:59.685
Sure.

17:01.520 --> 17:03.063
Gosh, I'm torn.

17:03.147 --> 17:04.940
What should I have first?

17:14.700 --> 17:15.659
Oh, eel…

17:19.663 --> 17:21.206
I noticed it last time too.

17:21.832 --> 17:24.918
Our personalities may be different,
but we have similar palates.

17:28.338 --> 17:31.175
Here. You can have some first.

17:31.967 --> 17:33.552
Then let's have one each to be fair.

17:49.359 --> 17:50.360
It's delicious.

18:37.950 --> 18:39.118
Come in.

18:42.204 --> 18:44.873
Shin I-rang has conceded the case.

18:46.583 --> 18:48.252
What else could they do?

18:48.335 --> 18:49.628
Instead,

18:49.711 --> 18:51.630
Cha Eun Seong filed a lawsuit

18:51.713 --> 18:55.050
against Ideal Shoes to claim the share
of his mother, Ryeo Seon Hwa.

18:55.759 --> 18:56.635
What?

19:03.142 --> 19:04.810
PETITION
PETITIONEE: KANG JI-HOON

19:04.893 --> 19:06.812
FOR PROVISIONAL INJUNCTION
ON PROFIT DISTRIBUTION

19:07.396 --> 19:09.481
Han Na-hyun.
So you really want to do this?

19:14.319 --> 19:17.573
Find where Ryeo Seon Hwa
is buried immediately.

19:17.656 --> 19:19.408
And get Cha Eun Seong's DNA sample.

19:19.491 --> 19:20.325
Excuse me?

19:20.409 --> 19:23.954
Most North Korean defectors
enter South Korea with a fake ID.

19:26.748 --> 19:30.294
I'm saying Ryeo Seon Hwa and Cha Eun Seong
may not be blood-related.

19:31.003 --> 19:34.256
What if the test result says
they are mother and son?

19:34.965 --> 19:36.633
Then we'll make it so they aren't.

19:37.426 --> 19:39.845
Are you actually asking me that?

19:40.554 --> 19:42.973
If I have to teach you
and do things myself all the time,

19:43.056 --> 19:45.017
what's your use in this company?

19:48.270 --> 19:49.813
What are you waiting for? Get to work!

19:49.897 --> 19:50.814
Yes, sir.

19:56.778 --> 19:58.322
Thank you.

20:03.493 --> 20:05.370
How's your health?

20:05.454 --> 20:07.915
I've gotten a lot better
thanks to your food.

20:07.998 --> 20:09.791
Oh, this is really nothing.

20:09.875 --> 20:11.752
They say food is the best medicine.

20:13.545 --> 20:16.131
I guess I-rang is busy.

20:16.715 --> 20:17.716
Yes.

20:17.799 --> 20:21.511
It's not a lot,
but he seems to be getting a few clients.

20:22.512 --> 20:26.266
I watched him defend his client
during the last trial.

20:28.060 --> 20:31.480
He was a little quirky, but persuasive.

20:34.691 --> 20:35.901
Just like Gi-jung.

20:39.279 --> 20:41.031
My doctor told me

20:42.532 --> 20:45.035
my heart could stop at any minute.

20:46.036 --> 20:47.537
Maybe that's why,

20:49.498 --> 20:51.208
but I can't stop thinking about Gi-jung.

20:52.501 --> 20:54.294
I feel like I missed something.

20:54.878 --> 20:56.755
I noticed some holes in the case too.

20:58.382 --> 20:59.716
I have regrets.

21:01.885 --> 21:04.554
I told you not to bother.

21:04.638 --> 21:06.890
I just can't accept it myself.

21:08.016 --> 21:11.270
If there's any way to clear his name,

21:12.562 --> 21:14.231
I want to do it before I die.

21:16.233 --> 21:17.276
Did he

21:18.110 --> 21:20.237
leave any records behind?

21:21.113 --> 21:22.114
Records?

21:22.197 --> 21:23.824
Yes, you know

21:24.449 --> 21:26.702
that he always kept notes of everything.

21:27.619 --> 21:31.665
But the case materials didn't include
any of his notebooks

21:31.748 --> 21:34.209
or key materials about the case.

21:34.835 --> 21:35.711
So

21:36.461 --> 21:39.339
I was wondering if he
had them stored in private.

21:40.924 --> 21:42.259
I'm not sure.

21:43.385 --> 21:47.097
I do have a storage box he left at home.

21:48.223 --> 21:50.267
But I didn't see any records inside.

21:50.350 --> 21:52.102
Nor any notebooks.

21:52.686 --> 21:53.562
Oh.

21:54.688 --> 21:55.981
I see.

22:42.569 --> 22:44.654
HANDWRITTEN WILL, HEIR: KANG JI-HOON,
CONDITIONAL BENEFICIARY…

22:44.738 --> 22:45.822
MALLI-DONG (1980), MALLI-DONG (2025)

22:47.449 --> 22:51.369
THE THREE CO-FOUNDERS

22:56.500 --> 22:59.002
THANK YOU, JEONG-HUI

22:59.086 --> 23:04.424
Ms. Ryeo's message shows
that she's aware of Ms. Chae's intentions.

23:05.425 --> 23:07.552
I wonder why she's in hiding.

23:08.762 --> 23:11.640
Even by keeping it from her own son.

23:11.723 --> 23:14.976
Shoes are usually more comfortable

23:15.060 --> 23:17.104
when they're soft.

23:17.187 --> 23:18.313
However,

23:18.897 --> 23:23.110
in dangerous places
like construction sites,

23:23.193 --> 23:26.780
stiff and uncomfortable shoes are

23:26.863 --> 23:29.908
what keep your feet safe.

23:31.201 --> 23:32.077
Excuse me?

23:32.160 --> 23:35.163
Whoever that woman is,

23:35.247 --> 23:40.460
she may be hiding herself in stiff shoes.

23:42.003 --> 23:43.547
To be safe?

23:44.548 --> 23:45.382
Exactly.

23:55.600 --> 23:57.102
RE: REQUEST ON PUBLIC DEFENDER RECORDS

23:58.937 --> 24:00.105
LEE JEONG-SU

24:02.107 --> 24:05.026
I'M CONTACTING YOU REGARDING YOUR EMAIL
I REMEMBER MS. RYEO SEON HWA

24:09.990 --> 24:12.617
Hello? I'm calling
about the email you sent.

24:15.829 --> 24:17.247
Yes. Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa.

24:20.167 --> 24:21.042
Oh.

24:21.626 --> 24:26.298
Attorney Lee Jeong-su was
a public defender his entire career.

24:27.340 --> 24:30.677
He retired a long time ago.
Now, he's fighting terminal cancer.

24:31.344 --> 24:33.722
Our visit may end up fruitless.

24:33.805 --> 24:38.226
No, he wouldn't have even emailed me
if he didn't have anything to tell us.

24:42.147 --> 24:44.149
GARAM HOSPICE

24:47.360 --> 24:50.906
Ms. Ryeo has a son who was separated
from her when he was one year old.

24:50.989 --> 24:54.743
Do you remember anything about her?

24:55.702 --> 24:59.706
She was quiet and taciturn.

25:00.957 --> 25:05.253
Still, I could tell
she was resolute and upright.

25:06.463 --> 25:08.465
But that's all I know.

25:09.049 --> 25:11.968
If you want to know more about her,

25:12.594 --> 25:17.349
you'd better ask her former co-inmates.

25:18.558 --> 25:20.852
We had the same idea,

25:20.936 --> 25:22.938
but no records were left in the prison.

25:24.147 --> 25:28.610
There was one more female inmate
whom I defended.

25:29.569 --> 25:33.949
I remember she was a cellmate of Ms. Ryeo.

25:34.532 --> 25:36.952
Do you remember her name?

25:39.579 --> 25:42.123
Oh, can you open that cabinet?

25:43.792 --> 25:44.793
You mean this one?

25:44.876 --> 25:46.753
Yes, check the notebooks inside.

25:47.921 --> 25:49.422
Her number should be written there.

25:54.386 --> 25:55.845
Thank you, sir.

25:55.929 --> 25:57.472
It's my pleasure.

25:59.391 --> 26:04.771
Thank you for letting me do
something good for Ms. Ryeo before I die.

26:07.357 --> 26:10.193
GARAM HOSPICE

26:11.111 --> 26:12.946
Finding people is Bong-su's expertise.

26:13.655 --> 26:14.990
Let me try calling him.

26:17.117 --> 26:20.370
Baby, don't leave me like this.

26:20.996 --> 26:23.456
Ji-a and I can't survive without you.

26:24.291 --> 26:25.166
I'm sorry.

26:26.293 --> 26:28.128
I wanted to protect you to the end…

26:39.597 --> 26:40.974
Where's that coming from?

26:41.683 --> 26:42.559
Where…

26:45.645 --> 26:46.521
Cut!

26:47.105 --> 26:50.108
-Cut.
-Whose phone is ringing?

26:50.191 --> 26:51.526
Where is it coming from?

26:51.609 --> 26:52.485
Tell me where!

26:54.112 --> 26:55.655
Goodness, gracious.

26:55.739 --> 26:57.532
-Whose phone is it?
-What the heck?

26:57.615 --> 27:00.160
-You've got to be kidding me.
-Whose phone is this?

27:00.243 --> 27:01.619
Give it a rest.

27:01.703 --> 27:03.121
-What the…
-Unbelievable.

27:05.373 --> 27:06.541
Okay, I-rang.

27:06.624 --> 27:10.378
I lost my gig thanks to you.
I'll get on it as soon as I go home.

27:33.401 --> 27:34.694
I found it, sir.

27:34.778 --> 27:38.073
I came to where CEO Kang's mother visited
with his driver sometimes.

27:38.156 --> 27:40.283
There's a grave mound
that seems to be Ms. Ryeo's here.

27:40.909 --> 27:42.494
File a petition for an autopsy,

27:42.577 --> 27:45.538
and request Cha Eun Seong
an official DNA test now.

27:46.122 --> 27:47.332
A DNA test?

27:50.710 --> 27:53.129
All right. I'll get back to you.

28:05.475 --> 28:08.728
Taebaek has requested
a maternity DNA test.

28:09.229 --> 28:12.315
Attorney Yang must have found
Ms. Ryeo's grave.

28:13.608 --> 28:15.026
What a smart move.

28:15.568 --> 28:19.489
This suit is said to be
for interim profit distribution,

28:19.572 --> 28:21.866
but it actually is
an inheritance dispute lawsuit.

28:22.450 --> 28:25.537
If Ms. Ryeo is alive
like Ms. Chae assumes,

28:25.620 --> 28:27.539
the test result will be negative.

28:29.499 --> 28:32.585
But it's not like we can refuse
to do the test.

28:34.879 --> 28:38.258
Now, our only way to win this suit
is to find Ms. Ryeo.

28:38.842 --> 28:40.468
Did you hear from your brother-in-law?

28:40.552 --> 28:43.388
Yes, he got her current number
and talked to her on the phone.

28:44.055 --> 28:45.473
Does she remember Ms. Ryeo?

28:45.557 --> 28:47.976
Yes, she said they were co-inmates.

28:48.685 --> 28:51.312
Bong-su said he took off.
We should get going too.

28:51.896 --> 28:52.731
Okay.

28:57.110 --> 28:59.446
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

29:34.397 --> 29:38.318
Who are you and why look for someone
who died more than 40 years ago?

29:40.403 --> 29:42.238
I'm Attorney Shin I-rang.

29:43.406 --> 29:46.743
Ms. Ryeo's son
wants to know about his mother.

29:47.327 --> 29:49.662
I didn't know she had a son.

29:50.622 --> 29:54.167
But then again, she had a lot of secrets.

29:55.043 --> 30:00.215
Could you tell us
how Ms. Ryeo passed away in detail?

30:02.008 --> 30:04.552
There was a fire
in the prison laundry room.

30:06.179 --> 30:09.766
Seon Hwa and Sun-yeong were taken
to a hospital with severe burns.

30:10.850 --> 30:13.353
None of them came back.

30:13.436 --> 30:16.773
Are you saying they're both dead?

30:20.443 --> 30:21.694
Seon Hwa died,

30:22.695 --> 30:25.782
Sun-yeong got treated at the hospital
for a few weeks

30:26.491 --> 30:28.827
and finished her time there.

30:31.412 --> 30:33.706
Are you still in touch
with this Sun-yeong?

30:34.415 --> 30:35.416
No.

30:36.960 --> 30:39.128
We have no good reason to stay in touch.

30:52.892 --> 30:54.853
Are we on the same page?

30:55.895 --> 30:58.773
That Sun-yeong may be Ms. Ryeo?

31:00.900 --> 31:03.570
If Ms. Ryeo really is alive,

31:04.112 --> 31:05.738
the chances are high.

31:17.208 --> 31:19.878
If they both got burns on their faces

31:20.503 --> 31:22.505
and given that it was 50 years ago,

31:23.298 --> 31:26.050
faking identities would've been possible
just by changing uniforms.

31:26.134 --> 31:27.260
PARK SUN-YEONG
FEMALE, BURN

31:27.343 --> 31:28.761
On top of that,

31:28.845 --> 31:31.848
it would've been easier
if the fire destroyed the records.

31:32.432 --> 31:35.018
We just need to find this woman
named Sun-yeong.

31:35.852 --> 31:37.353
But how and where?

31:39.981 --> 31:40.899
Beats me.

31:42.817 --> 31:45.528
Anyway, where's Mr. Kang?

32:08.217 --> 32:11.220
She seems humble and kind-hearted.

32:15.058 --> 32:17.477
Why was she shaking her leg?

32:18.895 --> 32:20.813
Was she anxious about something?

32:27.153 --> 32:30.323
EUNSEON NOODLES
PARK SUN-YEONG

32:36.871 --> 32:38.748
Hello? Seon Hwa?

32:40.041 --> 32:41.751
Some people are looking for you.

32:42.335 --> 32:43.461
Run away.

32:47.131 --> 32:48.257
Wait.

32:48.341 --> 32:49.676
It's Seon Hwa!

32:50.760 --> 32:52.220
It's her.

32:52.845 --> 32:53.721
Goodness.

32:57.850 --> 32:59.769
Oh, here he comes.

33:00.478 --> 33:01.604
Quick, let's go.

33:03.064 --> 33:03.940
Let's go.

33:04.524 --> 33:06.526
-Go where?
-The noodle restaurant.

33:07.151 --> 33:09.195
Seon Hwa is there.

33:10.029 --> 33:10.863
Really?

33:11.447 --> 33:12.657
What is it? What does he say?

33:13.282 --> 33:15.118
He says Ms. Ryeo is
at the noodle restaurant.

33:16.077 --> 33:18.830
Why would Ms. Ryeo be there?

33:21.666 --> 33:23.543
You're having a late lunch today.

33:23.626 --> 33:25.420
It's not good to skip meals.

33:26.004 --> 33:28.047
Come by anytime.

33:28.131 --> 33:29.257
Okay?

33:29.924 --> 33:32.260
And eat up.

33:32.844 --> 33:33.803
Ma'am.

33:41.936 --> 33:43.521
-The old lady there?
-The old lady there?

33:48.568 --> 33:50.653
Seon Hwa,

33:50.737 --> 33:52.655
please don't run away.

33:53.865 --> 33:56.826
You should at least let her apologize.

34:19.849 --> 34:24.145
EUNSEON NOODLES

34:33.988 --> 34:34.989
Excuse me!

34:36.157 --> 34:37.408
Anyone inside?

34:38.367 --> 34:40.453
-Attorney Shin?
-Oh.

34:41.037 --> 34:44.040
Mr. Cha, didn't the owner lady
come to work today?

34:44.123 --> 34:46.751
Well, she did.

34:47.293 --> 34:49.754
She was busy working until lunch hours,

34:49.837 --> 34:51.839
but she suddenly closed shop
and rushed out.

34:53.174 --> 34:54.675
She rushed out?

34:54.759 --> 34:55.760
Yes.

35:08.940 --> 35:11.651
When did she leave? Was it just now?

35:12.235 --> 35:14.570
Yes, what's wrong?

35:14.654 --> 35:17.156
We'll explain later.

35:17.240 --> 35:18.116
Let's go.

35:21.119 --> 35:22.203
I-rang!

35:22.286 --> 35:23.329
Bong-su!

35:23.913 --> 35:25.164
Turn the truck around. Back!

35:25.248 --> 35:26.374
Back? Back where?

35:26.999 --> 35:28.626
I have no time to explain. Follow us.

35:28.709 --> 35:29.710
Okay.

35:38.845 --> 35:40.429
Ms. Choi must've called her.

35:41.013 --> 35:43.516
I wonder why she's trying this hard
to hide herself.

35:50.481 --> 35:51.691
What do we do?

35:52.942 --> 35:55.278
We'll go to the left. Can you go right?

35:55.361 --> 35:56.529
Okay.

36:11.502 --> 36:14.338
I don't remember any other roads here.
Maybe she went left.

36:23.931 --> 36:26.142
Oh, there. It's over there.

36:53.753 --> 36:56.923
Do we have the right to do this?

36:59.050 --> 37:02.428
She barely made it back alive

37:03.012 --> 37:05.097
and cooked for her son in secret.

37:06.390 --> 37:09.769
If not for us,
she can still be around her son.

37:10.561 --> 37:11.854
But we're chasing her away.

37:13.064 --> 37:13.981
Do we

37:14.774 --> 37:16.484
really have the right to do this?

37:17.902 --> 37:19.820
I understand how you feel.

37:24.367 --> 37:26.535
Let me go and talk to her alone.

37:26.619 --> 37:30.665
I'll get her take on this,
and if she says no, I'll let her go.

37:56.732 --> 37:57.566
Hello.

37:59.819 --> 38:00.653
Who are you?

38:02.029 --> 38:03.781
I'm Attorney Han Na-hyun.

38:04.991 --> 38:06.575
You're Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa, aren't you?

38:08.286 --> 38:10.955
I'm not. You got the wrong person.

38:11.038 --> 38:12.873
Why did you pretend that you were dead

38:14.083 --> 38:16.002
when you weren't?

38:17.461 --> 38:19.088
You even kept it from your son.

38:23.009 --> 38:24.593
I guess you're looking for someone.

38:25.886 --> 38:27.054
But wouldn't that person

38:27.847 --> 38:29.515
have her own circumstances?

38:30.308 --> 38:32.184
Everyone has circumstances.

38:34.353 --> 38:35.771
And it includes Ms. Chae Jeong-hui.

38:38.065 --> 38:43.070
To give Mr. Cha Eun Seong
shares of Ideal Shoes,

38:43.154 --> 38:47.116
she even faked the will of her husband
who suffered from Alzheimer's.

38:48.326 --> 38:49.577
A fake will?

38:49.660 --> 38:50.661
Why did Jeong-hui…

38:54.081 --> 38:58.336
She believes she caused your death.

38:59.837 --> 39:02.006
She thought you got arrested

39:02.089 --> 39:04.550
because of what she said to the police.

39:05.217 --> 39:07.011
She's lived in repentance for 50 years.

39:09.889 --> 39:12.224
I wanted to let you know.

39:15.686 --> 39:18.522
I'll forget that I saw you here.

39:18.606 --> 39:19.440
Goodbye.

39:21.484 --> 39:22.735
Wait.

39:31.494 --> 39:32.370
Ms. Chae!

39:32.453 --> 39:33.829
Oh, hey.

39:35.915 --> 39:36.832
We found her.

39:39.001 --> 39:40.378
We found

39:41.170 --> 39:42.213
Ms. Ryeo Seon Hwa.

40:07.446 --> 40:08.531
Wait.

40:37.184 --> 40:38.102
Seon Hwa…

40:39.395 --> 40:40.312
Jeong-hui.

40:40.896 --> 40:43.607
Seon Hwa. You're alive.

40:46.694 --> 40:48.779
I thought you were dead.

40:49.947 --> 40:51.115
I'm not dead.

40:52.741 --> 40:54.326
I couldn't die.

40:56.287 --> 40:57.329
Seon Hwa.

40:59.957 --> 41:01.125
I'm sorry.

41:02.209 --> 41:03.252
I'm sorry, Seon Hwa.

41:04.795 --> 41:07.298
I'm to blame for everything
you've been through.

41:07.840 --> 41:09.633
I'm so sorry.

41:09.717 --> 41:11.385
I was such a fool.

41:12.678 --> 41:13.971
No.

41:14.054 --> 41:15.723
It's not your fault.

41:17.766 --> 41:19.685
The attorney told me

41:19.768 --> 41:21.687
what you were mistaken about.

41:23.606 --> 41:24.982
I decided to come here

41:25.649 --> 41:27.234
to clear up your misunderstanding.

41:27.985 --> 41:29.153
Misunderstanding?

41:29.862 --> 41:32.865
IDEAL SHOES

41:42.500 --> 41:46.587
Much before you met
that detective at the bar,

41:47.379 --> 41:50.216
I knew I was being watched.

41:52.885 --> 41:56.472
I meant to leave as soon as I got a letter
from my son who was escaping North Korea.

42:00.142 --> 42:01.810
But they moved faster.

42:02.353 --> 42:04.438
So even if not for you,

42:05.105 --> 42:07.233
I was destined to get arrested.

42:07.316 --> 42:08.859
Seon Hwa…

42:12.530 --> 42:14.240
Still, I'm sorry.

42:14.907 --> 42:16.367
I'm sorry. I really am.

42:17.159 --> 42:18.035
Thank you.

42:18.661 --> 42:21.205
Thank you for being alive.

42:27.836 --> 42:30.172
I'm sorry I couldn't be of help.

42:31.298 --> 42:32.299
Don't be.

42:32.925 --> 42:36.512
You're the one
who suggested we find Ms. Ryeo.

42:36.595 --> 42:39.598
You played a big part in their reunion.

42:39.682 --> 42:41.684
That's not true.

42:41.767 --> 42:44.103
You're the one who convinced Ms. Ryeo.

42:44.186 --> 42:46.063
So you played a much bigger part.

42:47.398 --> 42:48.399
Let's say I did then.

42:51.151 --> 42:52.820
Where's Mr. Kang?

42:55.447 --> 42:56.657
He's over there.

42:58.826 --> 43:01.704
He'd be happy to know what happened today.

43:04.248 --> 43:05.916
That seems unnecessary, though.

43:07.918 --> 43:09.128
I mean,

43:10.087 --> 43:14.133
his mind is in the splendid days
of when he was 20.

43:22.141 --> 43:23.767
They're so pretty.

43:34.945 --> 43:38.157
Why don't we go finish up the lawsuit?

43:39.783 --> 43:40.659
Sure.

43:55.382 --> 43:56.634
So,

43:57.176 --> 43:59.928
Ms. Ryeo is living someone else's life

44:00.554 --> 44:03.515
and if this suit continues,
her identity may be revealed?

44:04.099 --> 44:05.017
That's right.

44:05.559 --> 44:10.564
Attorney Yang goes to great lengths
for his own personal gain.

44:11.690 --> 44:15.694
If he discovers
Ms. Ryeo committed identity theft,

44:15.778 --> 44:18.572
he'll use it
to take the upper hand in the trial.

44:19.615 --> 44:21.617
Why are you telling me this?

44:22.618 --> 44:25.412
Did you forget that I'm the defendant?

44:28.374 --> 44:32.127
I thought you'd listen and consider.

44:33.212 --> 44:37.466
I happen to know you quite well.

44:40.761 --> 44:42.096
You know me?

44:43.347 --> 44:44.264
Yes.

44:44.890 --> 44:48.519
Someone told me what you were like.

44:51.063 --> 44:52.689
You must've talked with my mother.

44:52.773 --> 44:55.692
No, it was someone else.

44:58.028 --> 44:59.321
According to him,

44:59.905 --> 45:02.866
shoes hold the warmth
of whoever makes them.

45:04.201 --> 45:06.286
That your shoes are warm

45:07.079 --> 45:09.164
because they portray your heart.

45:12.876 --> 45:14.044
Let me see.

45:22.719 --> 45:24.930
What a warm pair of shoes.

45:26.640 --> 45:27.474
What?

45:27.558 --> 45:31.019
You made a pair of shoes
that are just like your heart.

45:33.147 --> 45:34.314
You see,

45:34.898 --> 45:39.194
shoes are bound to hold the warmth
of whoever makes them.

45:42.406 --> 45:43.991
You're better than me, brat.

45:44.533 --> 45:45.451
Here.

45:47.619 --> 45:48.620
Thank you.

46:12.853 --> 46:13.729
Let's go.

46:29.411 --> 46:31.413
DNA TEST RESULTS

46:31.497 --> 46:33.040
I told you.

46:33.874 --> 46:35.042
That if you wanted,

46:35.125 --> 46:37.711
I could help you not give
Cha Eun Seong a single coin.

46:38.712 --> 46:39.796
You've won.

46:43.217 --> 46:45.719
I'd like to end this suit here.

46:46.887 --> 46:48.055
Excuse me?

46:49.306 --> 46:51.808
End it here? No, we've won.

46:51.892 --> 46:54.686
I ran a thorough analysis of the leather
produced at Mr. Cha's factory.

46:55.270 --> 46:58.899
The result says a 100% match
with my company's leather production.

47:00.317 --> 47:05.197
I hear he uses a traditional family method
to produce the leather.

47:08.575 --> 47:09.826
I've decided to believe

47:11.870 --> 47:13.956
Mr. Cha's leather more than this paper.

47:14.957 --> 47:16.083
I appreciate your hard work.

47:16.917 --> 47:19.294
I'll wire the legal fees right away.

47:40.023 --> 47:41.733
Stop checking.

47:41.817 --> 47:44.403
All my vegetables are guaranteed fresh.

47:45.279 --> 47:46.238
There's a bug!

47:46.321 --> 47:47.781
What bug?

47:47.864 --> 47:49.741
These are organic. That's why.

47:49.825 --> 47:54.621
The presence of bugs mean no pesticides.

47:54.705 --> 47:55.956
Still…

47:56.540 --> 47:57.791
I'll take a bag of spinach.

47:57.874 --> 47:59.751
Of course.

48:00.544 --> 48:03.338
-You're buying some too?
-Yes, it looks fresh and delicious.

48:04.298 --> 48:05.382
And…

48:06.717 --> 48:07.843
Consider these

48:08.635 --> 48:10.596
a little extra for you today.

48:11.471 --> 48:12.806
Thank you.

48:12.889 --> 48:14.600
What the… Ms. Chae.

48:14.683 --> 48:15.559
What?

48:16.184 --> 48:17.561
That's unusual of you.

48:18.145 --> 48:19.313
Ji-hoon

48:20.981 --> 48:24.526
signed a leather supply contract
with Seon Hwa's son.

48:26.695 --> 48:29.865
This is all thanks to you attorneys.

48:31.199 --> 48:32.200
I'm glad to hear that.

48:32.784 --> 48:33.619
Thanks.

48:35.370 --> 48:36.330
Oh, right.

48:36.830 --> 48:41.877
I'm visiting my husband
with Seon Hwa today.

48:44.379 --> 48:48.091
Seon Hwa…

48:48.717 --> 48:50.719
Oh, I shouldn't call her by that name.

48:50.802 --> 48:51.720
Silly me.

48:54.598 --> 48:57.809
Sun-yeong, I'm on my way now.

49:04.524 --> 49:06.943
I'll take off soon too.

49:12.616 --> 49:14.701
-Are you going somewhere?
-Yes.

49:14.785 --> 49:16.036
To do some business.

49:16.620 --> 49:17.996
And here I thought…

49:18.080 --> 49:20.499
I was worried you might leave
like the other day.

49:21.333 --> 49:22.793
Were you worried about me?

49:23.418 --> 49:24.252
Why?

49:26.797 --> 49:27.756
It's just

49:28.882 --> 49:30.342
that when I see you,

49:31.218 --> 49:32.552
I'm reminded of my mom.

49:36.765 --> 49:38.266
Do you remember your mom?

49:40.894 --> 49:43.814
I don't remember her face
because we parted ways when I was little.

49:45.816 --> 49:47.484
But when I have your noodles,

49:48.652 --> 49:50.529
it feels like my mom's cooking.

49:51.863 --> 49:53.031
I see.

49:55.409 --> 49:56.743
The truth is,

49:58.537 --> 50:00.038
seeing you

50:01.206 --> 50:03.291
often reminds me of my son.

50:05.293 --> 50:06.378
You have a son?

50:07.462 --> 50:08.296
Yes.

50:10.632 --> 50:12.342
We parted ways when he was little.

50:13.176 --> 50:15.262
He's about your age.

50:21.852 --> 50:23.729
Look, ma'am.

50:25.272 --> 50:28.316
I believe family isn't always about blood.

50:30.318 --> 50:32.362
I'm not suggesting anything grand.

50:32.446 --> 50:34.531
We could have dinner together
on national holidays,

50:34.614 --> 50:36.366
prepare a cake for each other's birthday,

50:36.450 --> 50:38.618
and look after each other when we're sick.

50:44.124 --> 50:47.085
Oh, I guess I crossed the line.

50:51.840 --> 50:53.175
Sounds good.

50:55.552 --> 50:56.386
What?

50:57.763 --> 50:59.139
I'd love that.

51:02.934 --> 51:04.060
From now on,

51:04.978 --> 51:06.521
call me Eun Seong.

51:09.191 --> 51:10.150
Eun Seong.

51:13.779 --> 51:15.197
I'm glad to have you with me.

51:16.281 --> 51:18.950
I'm glad to have you with me too,

51:20.786 --> 51:21.703
Mom.

51:38.762 --> 51:39.971
Hello?

51:41.264 --> 51:42.682
I see.

51:42.766 --> 51:44.351
Okay, bye.

51:46.144 --> 51:48.271
She's arrived.
She's in the bathroom right now.

51:48.355 --> 51:49.356
Oh.

51:49.981 --> 51:51.233
There she is.

51:52.776 --> 51:54.861
Enjoy your time. I'll wait here.

51:55.695 --> 51:58.740
Thank you for driving me here.

52:01.076 --> 52:02.118
We'll be right back.

52:13.797 --> 52:15.090
Honey.

52:15.674 --> 52:17.592
Seon Hwa is here.

52:26.351 --> 52:27.519
Dong-sik.

52:28.687 --> 52:30.564
It took me so long to come.

52:31.898 --> 52:32.899
I'm sorry.

52:35.569 --> 52:37.320
You must be happy

52:38.530 --> 52:41.324
to see her like this.

52:45.662 --> 52:46.538
Seon Hwa.

52:48.248 --> 52:49.374
I have

52:50.292 --> 52:52.419
something for you.

53:05.015 --> 53:06.850
To be precise,

53:07.601 --> 53:09.769
this gift is from Dong-sik, not me.

53:12.981 --> 53:16.359
These shoes aren't for me.

53:20.113 --> 53:20.989
Seon Hwa.

53:22.198 --> 53:23.700
I'm all right.

53:25.201 --> 53:26.328
I saw you

53:27.203 --> 53:30.790
with him at the workshop that day.

53:31.374 --> 53:32.876
No, that's…

53:32.959 --> 53:34.044
Wait.

53:36.087 --> 53:37.839
All right, look.

53:38.590 --> 53:39.424
See?

53:43.261 --> 53:45.597
Why are they small for you?

53:45.680 --> 53:46.514
Gosh.

53:47.223 --> 53:49.225
Go ahead and try them on.

53:52.604 --> 53:53.480
Me?

53:53.563 --> 53:54.981
Come now.

54:41.486 --> 54:42.821
He's so cool.

55:03.383 --> 55:04.509
She's so pretty.

55:07.679 --> 55:08.596
Jeong-hui.

55:09.723 --> 55:10.807
Dong-sik.

55:15.353 --> 55:16.813
You finally put them on.

55:16.896 --> 55:17.981
Your shoes.

55:19.107 --> 55:20.275
I didn't know.

55:22.444 --> 55:24.320
I thought they were for Seon Hwa.

55:25.030 --> 55:28.950
Your heels are sensitive
and blister easily.

55:29.868 --> 55:33.329
So, I asked Seon Hwa
for extra soft leather.

55:37.792 --> 55:38.835
These…

55:41.129 --> 55:42.672
were really for me?

55:51.264 --> 55:54.768
I made them in hopes
for you to come home anytime.

55:56.186 --> 55:59.606
I wanted to tell you that I'd always

56:01.232 --> 56:02.567
wait for you there.

56:05.320 --> 56:06.738
I had no idea.

56:07.781 --> 56:08.698
Jeong-hui.

56:11.117 --> 56:14.788
I'd pluck the stars and the moon for you,

56:15.914 --> 56:17.791
my beautiful Chae Jeong-hui.

56:21.294 --> 56:22.712
I loved you.

56:24.756 --> 56:25.673
And…

56:28.635 --> 56:30.261
I love you even now.

57:06.464 --> 57:07.674
Thank you.

57:09.134 --> 57:11.261
I owe a lot to you.

57:12.846 --> 57:13.972
Please don't mention it.

57:15.473 --> 57:18.226
Now that I met the person I needed to meet

57:18.810 --> 57:20.645
and gave what I needed to give,

57:21.271 --> 57:24.858
please help me pass on.

57:27.819 --> 57:30.321
You mean, here?

57:31.531 --> 57:33.700
Why? Can't I?

57:34.325 --> 57:35.702
Well…

57:35.785 --> 57:38.580
the priest is waiting on the rooftop.

57:39.414 --> 57:41.749
I'd like to pass on from here.

57:43.251 --> 57:46.421
I saw my wife's happy face.

57:47.046 --> 57:50.675
I'll be able to rest in peace
if I pass on from here.

57:53.511 --> 57:54.512
Sure.

57:59.893 --> 58:03.813
Father, please burn the talisman now.

58:03.897 --> 58:06.191
FATHER MA TAE-O

58:07.066 --> 58:07.984
Okay.

58:24.751 --> 58:25.752
Mr. Kang.

58:27.086 --> 58:29.297
Let me ask you one last question.

58:30.548 --> 58:31.424
What is it?

58:33.301 --> 58:36.721
How much do you remember?

58:38.765 --> 58:42.101
Sometimes, you seem like
you don't remember a thing.

58:42.852 --> 58:45.980
But at times, you seem like
you remember everything.

58:46.064 --> 58:48.107
What I remember

58:48.942 --> 58:50.151
is just one thing.

58:55.031 --> 58:56.324
Chae Jeong-hui.

58:57.158 --> 58:59.160
Her and her only.

59:02.872 --> 59:07.252
So you can say I remember everything.

59:09.087 --> 59:11.923
Remembering the love of your life

59:12.882 --> 59:15.802
means you remember everything.

59:21.266 --> 59:22.308
I see.

59:30.358 --> 59:31.276
Mr. Kang.

59:32.318 --> 59:33.570
Farewell.

59:34.153 --> 59:35.071
Goodbye.

59:36.447 --> 59:37.740
Take care.

01:00:13.568 --> 01:00:15.695
Come here, puppy!

01:00:32.378 --> 01:00:35.381
Mr. Kang passed on.

01:00:36.591 --> 01:00:37.592
Are you okay?

01:00:38.801 --> 01:00:40.803
I bet he grew on you a lot.

01:00:41.429 --> 01:00:45.600
He was deeply in love with Ms. Chae.

01:00:47.226 --> 01:00:48.353
But Ms. Chae

01:00:49.395 --> 01:00:51.564
wasn't aware of it her whole life.

01:00:52.815 --> 01:00:54.275
That really breaks my heart.

01:00:55.735 --> 01:00:56.903
I told you.

01:00:57.695 --> 01:01:00.782
If you save saying, "Thank you,"
"I'm sorry," or "I love you,"

01:01:00.865 --> 01:01:02.617
you'll regret it later.

01:01:03.576 --> 01:01:06.079
If you don't want to regret it later,

01:01:06.162 --> 01:01:07.997
express your feelings while you can.

01:01:14.712 --> 01:01:15.630
What's wrong?

01:01:19.133 --> 01:01:21.803
I won't regret it…

01:01:23.179 --> 01:01:26.432
Yes, I know.
You're not one to regret things later.

01:01:26.516 --> 01:01:28.017
…because I'm going to tell you now.

01:01:30.311 --> 01:01:31.312
What?

01:01:34.190 --> 01:01:35.108
I want to tell you

01:01:36.234 --> 01:01:37.318
how I feel

01:01:38.653 --> 01:01:39.904
right now.

01:02:07.849 --> 01:02:09.475
Puppy!

01:02:10.601 --> 01:02:11.853
Puppy?

01:02:13.980 --> 01:02:15.148
No way.

01:02:17.150 --> 01:02:18.401
Play with me.

01:02:20.945 --> 01:02:22.029
What's your name?

01:02:24.282 --> 01:02:27.034
Why couldn't he finish what he was saying?

01:02:27.118 --> 01:02:28.286
I'm so curious.

01:02:28.995 --> 01:02:30.329
Fine, go.

01:02:32.707 --> 01:02:34.083
You're adorable.

01:02:43.885 --> 01:02:46.804
THANK YOU, JEONG-HUI

01:02:58.900 --> 01:03:00.026
What's the matter, mister?

01:03:00.109 --> 01:03:02.653
I'm dying
because I have so many questions.

01:03:02.737 --> 01:03:03.696
I don't remember.

01:03:03.780 --> 01:03:05.490
An elementary student
was reported missing.

01:03:05.573 --> 01:03:07.116
He's a first grader.
He was wearing yellow rain boots.

01:03:07.200 --> 01:03:09.243
A boy in yellow rain boots.

01:03:09.327 --> 01:03:11.746
-Will I get to find my mom and dad soon?
-Please find him!

01:03:11.829 --> 01:03:14.832
A golf ball? It may be
an important clue about where he died.

01:03:14.916 --> 01:03:16.250
I found out who the boy is.

01:03:17.710 --> 01:03:19.545
Mister, watch out!

01:03:19.629 --> 01:03:21.172
Wake up!

01:03:21.255 --> 01:03:26.177
Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim
